==========================================================================================================

displaying the value of undfined character /;

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
<p id="demo"></p>
<script>
let x = 10 / "Hello";
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = Boolean(x);    
</script>    
</body>    
</html>

==========================================================================================================

Booleans and Boolean objects cannot be safely compared

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
<p id="demo"></p>
<script>
let x = false;
let y = new Boolean(false);
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = typeof x + "<br>" + typeof y;    
</script>    
</body>    
</html>


==========================================================================================================

Booleans and Boolean objects cannot be safely compared

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
<p id="demo"></p>
<script>
let x = false;
let y = new Boolean(false);
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = (x==y);    
</script>    
</body>    
</html>

